
## Users
Contains all endpoints related to the API for Users.

### - Get Current User
```shell
# Replace `token` with your invitation token
# Replace `PUBLIC_KEY` with your public key
curl -X GET -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "api-version: 1" https://dev-api.causemo.com/app/users/me -u <PUBLIC_KEY>:
```
```javascript
var appAPI = require('causemo-api-client').appAPI; // get app API
var userAPI = appAPI.user; // get User endpoint 
var authToken = ....;
return userAPI.getUserInfoForToken(authToken)
  .then(console.log.bind(undefined))
  .catch(console.error.bind(undefined));
```
Fetch current user information

* **URL:** `/app/users/me`
* **METHOD:** GET
* **TYPE:** public

### - Update Current User 
```shell
# Replace `token` with your invitation token
# Replace `PUBLIC_KEY` with your public key
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "api-version: 1" -d '{...} https://dev-api.causemo.com/app/users/me -u <PUBLIC_KEY>:
```
```javascript
var appAPI = require('causemo-api-client').appAPI; // get app API
var userAPI = appAPI.user; // get User endpoint 
var userObj = {...};
return userAPI.updateCurrentUser(authToken, userObj)
  .then(console.log.bind(undefined))
  .catch(console.error.bind(undefined));
```
Updates the current user information using the provided user object.

* **URL:** `/app/users/me`
* **METHOD:** POST
* **TYPE:** public

#### BODY:
Parameter | Required | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
firstName | true | User first name
lastName | true | User last name
title | false | User job title
tmpAvatar | false | The temporary S3 location for the user avatar
password | false | User password, only needed if password changed

